a simple data transmission system using the office telephone.wa method has evolved for transmitting data ofa type originating in many laboratory situation direct to a central computer.  the method requires almostno specialized equipment and uses any ordinary telephone on a "callup" basis.  present applicationsinclude cardiac-output calculations, radio-activity tracer studies and neurophysiology time-sequence studies of nerve impulses.cacm october, neilsen, i. r.ca jb march ,   : pm